Step 1: Identify Total Liabilities and Total Assets at the end of the reporting period.
• Total Liabilities in this problem are given as "Total Current Liabilities": 2491297.55.
• Total Assets are provided as: 14089860.66.

Step 2: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio using the formula:
  Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets

Calculation:
  = 2491297.55 / 14089860.66 
  ≈ 0.1768

Step 3: Round the result to two decimal places:
  ≈ 0.18

Thus, the Debt to Asset Ratio is approximately 0.18.
